description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are delighted to invite applications for the post of consultant neurologist for the Frimley Park Hospital site, with sessions at St George’s hospital. The successful appointee will work alongside 4 other consultants in a welcoming and forward looking department, with responsibilities for outpatient and inpatient care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We provide a full range of services including MS therapies and Botulinum toxin treatments and have excellent imaging and neurophysiology facilities. The Frimley Health Integrated Care System allows coordinated working with community services and opportunities for developing patient-centred care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The hospital is rated Outstanding by the CQC. An interest in developing acute neurology and headache services or movement disorders would be desirable, but not essential. Participation in teaching of trainees and medical students will be expected.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Two days most weeks will be at the regional neurosciences centre, St George’s Hospital and St George’s University of London, where the appointee can develop a specialist clinic and participate in educational activities including a vibrant Grand Round. (For one in four weeks the appointee will spend 4 days at Frimley Park).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please see the full Job Description and Person Specification. Candidates are welcome to arrange a visit. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Jeremy SternJob titleConsultant NeurologistEmail addressjeremy.stern@nhs.netTelephone number01753 806 721Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dr Gareth Roberts, Interim Chief of Service for the Division of Medicine, 01753 633388. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
